parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including loss of power, malfunctioning of critical systems, and even fires, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
causing problems with the alarm system
directionals
interior lights
exterior lights
heater
and other electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's ignition system malfunctions
causing problems with the ignition switch
relays
and fuses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the vehicle's electrical system can cause a fire, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle's electrical system
causing damage to the fuse box
relays
and other components
which can lead to a fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake lights can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake lights fail to function properly
causing problems with the vehicle's safety features.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle shutting down in moving traffic can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power and shuts down while in motion
with no warning signs or indication of a problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the retainer clip on the clutch cable can cause the vehicle to lose acceleration, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stops accelerating
the clutch pedal feels stuck or stuck to the floor
the vehicle is unable to move or has delayed movement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or hesitation can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating
the vehicle slows down or loses power when driving
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The temporary lock-up of the steering wheel can lead to loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving on wet roads or navigating corners.
symptoms: The steering wheel locks up temporarily
making it difficult to maneuver
especially when driving on wet roads or navigating corners.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Frequent brake replacements can lead to increased stopping distances, which can cause accidents, and may result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The brakes need frequent replacements
the vehicle fails its yearly inspection due to brake issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission issues can cause unexpected acceleration or deceleration, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission continues to give problems
unexpected acceleration or deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tie rod failure can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents, and may result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle fails its yearly inspection due to tie rod issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent window operation and faulty alarm systems can be a nuisance and may lead to safety issues if the windows get stuck in an open or closed position.
symptoms: The passenger's side windows go up and down intermittently
the vehicle locks without prior warning
the alarm system is not operable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power convertible top can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to water damage or other issues if not addressed.
symptoms: The power top fails to operate
the top becomes stuck
or the top does not close properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent electrical system failures can cause a range of issues, from inconvenience to safety risks, as critical systems may fail to function properly.
symptoms: Intermittent failure of the cruise control
speedometer
tachometer
and radio; failure of the 6 CD changer; and sudden loss of power to the radio.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and failure can cause accidents, especially if the vehicle loses power while in motion.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies while driving
often at low speeds
and may cause the vehicle to coast to the side of the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Smog pump failure can cause damage to the vehicle's electrical system and potentially lead to a fire hazard.
symptoms: The smog pump fails
causing the harness wiring to char.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, including malfunctioning accessories, faulty warning lights, and even safety risks such as short circuits or fires.
symptoms: Malfunctioning accessories (e.g.
seat heaters
power windows
volume control)
faulty warning lights (e.g.
check engine light
ABS light)

battery explosions
and other electrical-related issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Problems with the convertible top can lead to cosmetic damage, water leaks, and even safety risks if the top malfunctions while driving.
symptoms: Black substance accumulating on the convertible top
hardening and becoming difficult to remove
malfunctioning hydraulic pump
and other issues related to the convertible top.

symptoms: Timing belt failure
exhaust system failure
brake system malfunctions

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air conditioning system failures can cause discomfort and inconvenience, especially during hot weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system malfunctions can lead to safety risks, including increased stopping distances and loss of control.
